      "content": "interesting. you mentioned Rushton and Jensen. some of the people in the forums i'm reading argue that the environmental explanations (like nutrition or school quality) are just \"cover stories\" because they don't fully account for the persistent gaps even when those things are controlled for. can you explain the logic they use to argue that genetics must be the primary driver despite the criticism?",
