      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense from their perspective. what about the \"evolutionary psychology\" angle that some of these researchers take? they sometimes talk about how different climates or survival pressures in different parts of the world might have selected for different levels of intelligence or social behavior. how do they connect those evolutionary pressures to the current racial gaps we see in testing?",
